# Advanced Options (optional)
#
# Disable WiFi power save (increases power consumption but improves latency):
# Add to network block: ps_mode=0
#
# Background scanning:
# bgscan="simple:30:-65:300"
#
# For WPA-Enterprise (requires additional configuration):
# network={
#     ssid="EnterpriseNetwork"
#     key_mgmt=WPA-EAP
#     eap=PEAP
#     identity="username"
#     password="password"
#     phase2="auth=MSCHAPV2"
# }

# Notes:
# - Only 2.4 GHz networks are supported (Pi Zero W does not support 5 GHz)
# - Raspberry Pi Zero W supports 802.11 b/g/n
# - For best security, use WPA2-PSK with AES encryption
# - The wpa_supplicant service will automatically start on boot via /etc/init.d/S40network
# - To restart networking: /etc/init.d/S40network restart
# - To check connection status: wpa_cli status
# - To scan for networks: iw dev wlan0 scan
